  <h1>Working with the IRI Flow and Database Models and
  Diagrams</h1>

  <p>The IRI Workbench now supports a work flow modeling tool and
  diagrams to help you design and build your data integration jobs.
  You will be working with the Sirius diagrams for Flow and ER
  models.</p>

  <h2>How do I create a flow model?</h2>

  <p><strong>Set up your project:</strong></p>

  <ol>
    <li>In the Project Explorer, right-click on your project and
    select <strong>Configure</strong> -&gt; <strong>Convert to
    Modeling Project</strong>.</li>

    <li>Right-click the project again and select
    <strong>Configure</strong> -&gt; <strong>Add Xtext
    Nature</strong>.</li>
  </ol>

  <p><strong>Create a flow model in one of these two
  ways:</strong></p>

  <ol>
    <li>Use the "New Multi-Table Protect Job" wizard to create a
    basic data integration flow. This will create a flow model.
    Then just follow the steps below to add a diagram.</li>

    <li>Add a diagram as described below.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>OR</p>

  <ol>
    <li>To build an empty model to build to your preferences, press
    <code>&lt;CTRL&gt;N</code> to open the "New" wizard.</li>

    <li>In the <strong>Wizards</strong> field, type
    <code>flow</code> to select <strong>Flow Model</strong>, and
    then click <strong>Next</strong>.</li>

    <li>Select a parent folder from the list, enter a file name in
    the field, and then click <strong>Next</strong>.</li>

    <li>Select <strong>Batch</strong> from the list in the Model
    Object field, and then click <strong>Finish</strong>.</li>

    <li>Add a diagram as described below.</li>
  </ol>

  <p><strong>Complete project setup:</strong></p>

  <ol>
    <li>Right-click the project and select <strong>Viewpoints
    Selection</strong>.</li>

    <li>Select <strong>Flow</strong> in the viewpoints list. Note
    that more of this will be automated in future releases.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Flow Diagram</h2>

  <p>If you built an empty model:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>In the Project Explorer, expand the <code>*.flow</code>
    model.</li>

    <li>Right-click on <strong>Batch</strong> and select
    <strong>New Representation</strong> -&gt; <strong>new Flow
    Diagram</strong>.<br>
    A new diagram opens.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>For a block mapping diagram:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>Expand the *.flow model and navigate to a block
    (<code>Batch TestBatch</code>) inside of the flow.</li>

    <li>Right-click on the Block and select <strong>new
    Representation</strong> -&gt; <strong>new Flow
    Diagram</strong>.<br>
    The diagram opens.</li>
  </ol><!-- ************************************** -->

  <h2>ER Diagram Notes</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>First a database model must be created. To do this:

      <ol>
        <li>In the Project Explorer, select the project.</li>

        <li>In the select Data Source Explorer, select the tables
        to be included in the diagram.</li>

        <li>Right-click and select <strong>Generate DB
        Model</strong>.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>

    <li>A database model is placed in the selected project
    location.</li>

    <li>The model has a <code>.sqlschema</code> extension and
    contains the schema.</li>

    <li>The ER diagram can be added by selecting the
    <strong>Schema</strong> in the model file in the Project
    Explorer and right-clicking <strong>New Representation</strong>
    -&gt; <strong>new Entity Relationship diagram</strong>.</li>

    <li>The HomePage diagram is added by selecting the
    <strong>Database</strong> in the model file in the the Project
    Explorer and right-clicking <strong>New Representation</strong>
    -&gt; <strong>new HomePage</strong>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Flow popup menu</h2>

  <p>By right-clicking in the Flow diagram you can get to the Flow
  popup menu. Here you can select various useful features. Note
  that some items are context sensitive so they will only show up
  at certain times.</p>

  <p><strong>New items are being added.</strong></p>

  <h2>How to add elements to the diagrams</h2>

  <p>Select an element from the Flow Creation section of the
  Palette on the right and click in the diagram. The element is
  placed in the diagram. Use the connections in the Flow diagram to
  link items together.</p>

  <h2>Mapping diagram</h2>

  <p>The mapping diagram allows you to see the mapping and
  transform in an aesthetically pleasing way.</p>
